╭─ Assistant [MainThread@4014050] ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ Now I understand the issue better. The problem is that when a loop is entered via an `indirectbr`, it doesn't have a proper preheader because:                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ 1. `getLoopPreheader()` requires a single predecessor outside the loop that has exactly one successor (the loop header)                                                                                        │
│ 2. With `indirectbr`, the loop header can have multiple predecessors from outside the loop, or the predecessor might not be "legal to hoist into"                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ However, looking at the test failure more carefully, I see that the test expects the transformation to actually happen - it's not expecting the pass to skip the transformation entirely. The test shows that  │
│ after the transformation, blocks A and B should have their branches modified to point to a new `C.loopexit` block.                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ This suggests that my initial approach of just returning early when there's no preheader is too conservative. Instead, I need to understand why the transformation is failing and find a way to make it work   │
│ even without a traditional preheader.                                                                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Looking at the code again, the `handleDeadExits()` function is trying to create a split preheader to preserve reachability of dead exit blocks. But if there's no preheader, maybe we can use a different      │
│ approach.                                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Let me check what the actual issue is. The crash happens because `Preheader` is null and we call `Preheader->getTerminator()`. But maybe we don't actually need a preheader for this specific case?            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Looking at the reproducer:                                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ - Block C is unreachable (it has `unreachable` terminator)                                                                                                                                                     │
│ - Blocks A and B both branch to C with constant condition `true`                                                                                                                                               │
